  }, "That load is generated on demand or on schedule against one or more endpoints,\xA0one or more of your services or something that is\xA0not even on\xA0your service. You can generate load not only against something running within your infrastructure but something external as well to do statistical analysis based on the configuration that you gave it and so yeah the answer is yes the traffic flows through the sidecar."), mdx("h5", null, "If I say I have never scripted or built any scenarios for fortio or nighthawk. Let's say I'm a loadrunner, a neoload, or a k6 user, and I want to accomplish the same thing with them. So what is the journey on those load generator? is it the same thing you have to build a workflow of requests that you want to send in that scenario?"), mdx("div", {
    className: "answer"
